Description.LocalizedString: Her unique ability allowed her to solve even the most difficult cases.
The uniform made people nervous, but her positive nature put them at ease.
She needed to understand the supernatural to overcome it.
She spent so much time daydreaming that she began to see visions everywhere.
Even when she wasn’t working at the diner, she had a genuine desire to help others.
Her work at the diner and the nursing home meant she spent a lot of time on her feet.
He struggled with writer’s block for years, letting his insecurities take over.
His world was engulfed in darkness when his wife was taken by an unnatural force.
He ran through the wilderness, living a story he couldn’t remember writing.
His memories were lost in a fog and a pressure was building in his head.
He gratefully wore the dry shirt the FBI had found for him.
He sat in secondhand jeans as he answered their numerous questions.
The light in his eyes snuffed out, control was no longer his.
The jacket did not belong to him, but it fit all too well.
This wasn’t Alan. He struggled in vain.
The light in his eyes smoldered with inhuman rage.
The jacket did not belong to him, but he wore it nevertheless.
This wasn’t Alan. He screamed in vain.
